  <summary date="2005-12-07T19:43:10Z" status="Introduced in House">Transport Aircraft Fuel Tank Safety Act of 2005 - Directs the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to issue a final rule to require: (1) manufacturers of transport category aircraft to install fuel tank inerting systems on existing category aircraft that have fuel tanks with high flammability exposure and new aircraft; and (2) operators of transport category aircraft to retrofit existing transport category aircraft with fuel tank inerting systems.</summary>
